The paper deals with geometric algorithms and data structures, specifically for problems related to convex hulls and ray shooting among segments. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents new data structures and algorithms, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of interval trees suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The mention of "preprocessing" and "query time" suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the mention of "polylogarithmic factor" suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
